*gmp_perfect_power*

(PHP 7 >= 7.3.0, PHP 8)

gmp_perfect_power â€” Perfect power check

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  gmp_perfect_power(GMP|int|string $num): bool~

Checks whether {num} is a perfect power.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  A GMP object, an int, or a string that can be interpreted as a number
  following the same logic as if the string was used in |gmp_init| with
  automatic base detection (i.e. when {base} is equal to 0).

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns true if {num} is a perfect power, false otherwise.

